<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-03-31T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-03-31T03:00:00-05:00" n="58" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d58">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1111 Gemmell, Nina E./3:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-03-31T16:00:00+08:00">March 31, 1930—4
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received March 31—11:20 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>239. Hankow’s March 30, 8 p.m., and Shanghai’s March 30, 11 a.m.<note n="79" xml:id="d58fn79">Neither printed.</note> Following telegram
                            sent the Minister for Foreign Affairs today is being repeated to Hankow
                            and Shanghai: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“March 31. I have the honor to state that Miss N[ina] Earl [<hi rend="italic">Eleanor</hi>] Gemmell, American, is reported
                                    captured by Communists at Yuanchow, Kiangsi, and that other
                                    members of the mission are reported confined in Yuanchow which
                                    has been taken by Communists. It is requested that Your
                                    Excellency will be good enough to devise immediate liaison for
                                    the release of the Americans concerned.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>